<font color="#FF0000">THE ANTI-WAR MOVEMENT</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jan 11 20:47:25 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
The anti-war movement mad two dignificant mistakes.<br>
1. We did not clearly differentiate between the soldier<br>
who faught the war and the gov't who instigated and <br>
controlled the war. <br><br>
2. By not clearly differentiating the soldier from those<br>
who led the war, we focused our anger at the vet, instead of<br>
understanding his/her position.<br><br>
The anti-war movement should have emraced the Vet, supported<br>
them and condemned the gov't for sending so many to their<br>
death.Maybe if we did this, there would be more gov't funds for<br>
PTSD and Agent-Orange victims, and the illnesses from the<br>
Gulf war would be something that our gov't would be willing<br>
to recognize. We are willing to fund the bombs, fund the<br>
guns but not fund the vets.<br><br>

